Cookie Policy
We use cookies, anonymous identifiers, and similar technologies to make our services better and more personalized for you. These tools also help us understand how our apps, games, and services are used so we can improve them.
How We Use Cookies and Similar Technologies
When you visit our website, use our apps, or interact with our content, we use technologies like cookies to collect information. This helps us:
Make your experience better: Remember your preferences (like language) and make things easier to use.
Keep things secure: Verify who you are and protect against fraud.
Understand what you like: See how you use our services so we can improve and offer you content you'll enjoy.
What are Cookies?
Cookies are tiny text files stored on your computer or phone. They help websites remember things about you. You can learn more about them at www.allaboutcookies.org.
Types of Technologies We Use
We use a few different types of technologies, some of which may collect personal data. These include:
Essential Cookies: These are necessary for you to log in and use our services.
Functionality Cookies: These let us remember your choices and personalize your experience.
Performance Cookies: These help us understand how people use our services so we can make them better.
Marketing Cookies: These are used to show you ads that are relevant to your interests.
Who Uses These Technologies?
Both we and our partners (like advertisers and analytics providers) may use these technologies.
What if I Don't Want Cookies?
You can usually change your browser settings to block cookies, but this might affect how our services work.
For more details about specific technologies we use, please check the links below:
Facebook Audience Network
We may use Facebook Audience Network to show you ads on our platforms. This service uses technologies similar to cookies to learn about your preferences and deliver ads that may be more relevant to you. This information may include identifiers for mobile devices (like Android Advertising ID or Advertising Identifier for iOS).
Facebook Privacy Policy link
Google Analytics
We use cookies to better understand how people use our services. This helps us see things like how many people visit, which pages are popular, and where visitors come from. This information helps us improve our services and make them more useful for you.
Google Privacy Policy
Google Firebase
We use Google Firebase to get a better understanding of how people use our services. This tool gives us insights into things like overall usage and traffic patterns, helping us identify areas where we can make improvements for a better user experience.
Google Privacy Policy
Unity Ads
We may offer you the option to watch video ads from Unity Ads in exchange for in-game rewards. While we don't share your information with Unity Ads, they may collect and store information about your ad interactions. This helps them show you ads that might be more relevant to you.
Unity Privacy Policies
AdMob
We use Google AdMob to show ads in our mobile apps. This helps us earn revenue so we can continue to provide and improve our services. AdMob may collect and use your data to personalize ads and measure their effectiveness.
Google Privacy Policy
Applovin
We may use AppLovin to show you ads on our services. They use cookies to learn about your interests across different websites and apps, so you see ads that are more relevant to you. This information doesn't reveal your identity, but it helps us and our partners understand how well our advertising is working.
Applovin Privacy Policy
AppsFlyer
We use AppsFlyer, a tool that helps us understand how people find and use our services. This helps us see which marketing campaigns are working best and how we can improve our overall performance. AppsFlyer collects information about how you interact with our services, but this information is made anonymous and used only for statistical purposes.
AppsFlyer Privacy Policy
Facebook
We may use Facebook to show you ads for our games while you're playing other games. Facebook uses cookies to learn about your interests across different games and apps, allowing them to show you ads for our games that you might be interested in. While this information doesn't directly reveal your personal identity, it helps Facebook recognize you across different games to tailor ads effectively.
Facebook Privacy Policy
Ironsource
We partner with IronSource mediation to show ads in our apps. This helps us earn revenue so we can keep providing you with great games and services. IronSource may collect and use your data to personalize ads and measure their effectiveness.
Ironsource Privacy Policy
Mintegral
Mintegral uses cookies to personalize ads displayed in our service.
Mintegral Privacy Policy
Tapjoy
We use Tapjoy to bot show offers in our apps and to promote our games in third party apps. Tapjoy may collect and use your data to personalize ads.
Tapjoy Privacy Policy
Data Erasure
Data we collect are crucial for the game functionality and basic measurement. You have right to request deletion of your game account so the data we collect will be deleted. If you wish to do so, please,
send us an email to UserDataDeletion@w.aldagames.com with information about your account
. In case of our older games, data about your account are not stored anywhere on our servers so you can only delete your saved data in the game itself.
